The paratypes are similar to the holotype in both qualitative and metric characters (
Table 2
).

The eggs, laid freely, are spherical, with trunco-conical processes with an indented terminal disc (
Fig. 3
). In a measured egg the diameter is 56.1 μm without processes, 71.7 μm including the processes. In this same egg 32–33 processes are present around the circumference, about 140 in the hemisphere. The processes are 4.6–5.1 μm high with a basal diameter of 4.2–4.9 μm; the indented terminal disc has a diameter of 2.8–3.6 μm.

The surfaces of the processes are smooth; the egg shell has many small pores forming an irregular reticular design with very small meshes (
Fig. 3
).
